l,"updatedAt":1688708389871,"createdAt":1593729957399,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1619992943578,"text":"\u003cimg src=\"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1593729962i/29752866._SX540_.jpg\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1593729962i/29752867._SX540_.jpg\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI have to admit: this was a pretty painful to read. Ron Kovic's story is troubling and hard to believe it actually happened. The book goes back and forth between first-person perspective and third-person narrative. Ron Kovic gives the story of his life as a patriotic All-American youth, enlisting in the US Marine Corps with dreams of preserving the American way of life, serving horrific combat duty in Vietnam, and the shocking account living as a paralyzed veteran in 1970s America.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1593729962i/29752868._SX540_.jpg\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRon Kovic was able to articulate exactly how he felt throughout the book. He gives the reader a first-hand glimpse of his hardships of being paralyzed, his emotional highs and lows, dealing with the subpar healthcare system in the VA hospital network, and eventually becoming an outspoken member against the war in Vietnam. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1593729962i/29752869._SX540_.jpg\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI felt post-traumatic growth was a huge protective factor in his life. Throughout the book, no matter how bad things got, Ron Kovic was always telling himself things like \"I gotta get through this\" and \"I'm going to survive no matter what\". His mental resilience kept him from developing unhealthy coping mechanisms and spiraling downward to the point of no-return. It was troubling to read about the thousands of Vietnam veterans who returned damaged and broken, only to be discarded as trash by the government.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOverall this was a great read because of the reality-based narrative. The story is well put together, is insightful, and heartbreaking at the same time. I would recommend it. Thanks!","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1986675?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"vietnam","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1986675?shelf=vietnam"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3325688958"},"likeCount":43,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0},"User:5253785":{"id":5253785,"__typename":"User","legacyId":5253785,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1495541962i/5253785._UX200_CR0,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":1883,"viewerRelationshipStatus":null,"name":"Lyn","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/5253785-lyn","contributor":null,"followersCount":16615},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.1CaGI-1lRJnO5BUICVBqcQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.1CaGI-1lRJnO5BUICVBqcQ","__typename":"Review","creator":{"__ref":"User:5253785"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1669808274296,"createdAt":1484361315821,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1486184150390,"text":"This was a difficult, almost painful book to read.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRon Kovic was a United States Marine who did two tours of duty in Vietnam and then was tragically wounded, becoming paralyzed from the chest down for the rest of his life. Kovic delivers a powerful message about war and our government.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKovic’s 1976 novel describes his wounding in Vietnam and his dreadful time after that in VA hospitals. Kovic was also born on the fourth of July and grew up living the 1950s American dream with baseball and astronauts. His disillusionment and anger is understandable and his protests against the Nixon administration was inspiring.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis reminded me somewhat of Elie Wiesel’s \u003ca href=\"https://goodreads.com/book/show/1617.Night\" title=\"Night by Elie Wiesel\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eNight\u003c/a\u003e in that it describes such a nightmarish experience. As horrible as Kovic’s descriptions were, like Night, I felt like it was important to read, to honor his story and to recognize that the lessons he imparts, from experience, needs to be told.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1484361492i/21712234.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"306\" alt=\"description\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/5253785?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"books-to-recommend-to-my-son","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/5253785?shelf=books-to-recommend-to-my-son"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1876424305"},"likeCount":39,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0},"User:5931200":{"id":5931200,"__typename":"User","legacyId":5931200,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1313127112i/5931200._UX200_CR0,28,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":71,"viewerRelationshipStatus":null,"name":"Cyndie Todd","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/5931200-cyndie-todd","contributor":null,"followersCount":5},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.6aLsDsX2CPTNR9rE2XVxuA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodread