ve broken. Still a young man, he is crushed under the weight of desire for a life he knows he can never have after giving his all to his country. His depression comes in waves, but he finds he feels the least alone when he is with other veterans. They form a brotherhood of people who understand each other, and they join the anti-war movement in hopes of ending the war in Vietnam and bringing “the boys” home. He endures beatings from the police and arrest for exercising his first amendment rights, rights that he fought to uphold. Those who never fought in this war were angry at him for being against the war and he was repeatedly called a “commie”, AKA the people we were calling the enemy of this war. This is a quick and extremely powerful book. I don’t think you can read this book and not feel some level of anger. Americans need to take a look at our history of betraying veterans and do better, vote better and be kind to each other.","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/18350447?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"actual-bookshelf","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/18350447?shelf=actual-bookshelf"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/5666326148"},"likeCount":1,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0},"User:81812311":{"id":81812311,"__typename":"User","legacyId":81812311,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1525980873i/81812311._UY200_CR2,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":291,"viewerRelationshipStatus":null,"name":"Marco Beneventi","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/81812311-marco-beneventi","contributor":null,"followersCount":7},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1._OpPxQb58omd9uasikGcog":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1._OpPxQb58omd9uasikGcog","__typename":"Review","